413 at the call of the chair or the director. The office shall provide administrative and staff
424 support for the council within existing resources.
3 7. Compensation. Council members are entitled to reimbursement for expenses in
4 accordance with Title 5, chapter 379, which is paid in equal proportions from the Adult
5 Use Cannabis Regulatory Coordination Fund established in section 1102 and the Medical
6 Use of Cannabis Fund established in Title 22, section 2430.'
7 Amend the bill by inserting after section 4 the following:
8 'Sec. 5. Cannabis Advisory Council; staggered terms. Notwithstanding the
9 Maine Revised Statutes, Title 28-B, section 115, subsection 4, of the initial members
10 appointed to the Cannabis Advisory Council pursuant to Title 28-B, section 115, subsection
11 1, the first appointments made pursuant to subsection 1, paragraphs A, B, E and F are for
12 one-year terms; the 2nd appointments made pursuant to subsection 1, paragraphs A, B, E
13 and F are for 2-year terms; and all other appointments are for 3-year terms. An initial term
14 of one year may not be considered a full term for the purposes of limiting the number of
15 terms for which a member may serve.
16 Sec. 6. Appropriations and allocations. The following appropriations and
17 allocations are made.
